    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="483"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.504/1461</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chinese Minister</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sze</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-30">March 30,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note of September 1, 1933,<note
                        n="30" xml:id="d483fn30">
                        <ref target="frus1933v05#pg_845">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1933, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">v</hi>, p. 845</ref>.</note> regarding the cost of
                    repatriating to China Chinese refugees from Mexico, I have the honor to inform
                    you that I have not failed to bring the matter to the attention of my
                    Government.</p>
                <pb facs="0556" n="490" xml:id="pg_490"/>
                <p>I have now received a reply, instructing me to deliver to you $10,443.26 for this
                    purpose, and I take pleasure in enclosing herewith a check for this amount for
                    transmission to the Secretary of Labor.</p>
                <p>I take this opportunity to express to you the sincere thanks of my Government for
                    the considerate treatment shown by the American Government to the Chinese
                    refugees who have been forced to flee from Mexico.</p>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sao Ke Alfred Sze</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
